Here are the steps to ensure the flawless running of the tool:

Must have a python3 installed (Latest version preffered)
Download and install Tesseract-ocr from : https://github.com/UB-Mannheim/tesseract/wiki

Note: the frontend and backend folder are for organizing files in the repository and not representing the current tool structure
Clone the repository and make sure Folders inside frontend folder that is static and templates will be in same directory as main.py and requirements.

Note: Given instructions are as per windows operating system
In terminal: 
Setup a virtual environment: python -m venv venv
acitvate the virtual environment: venv\Scripts\activate
install the required libraries of python as per: python -m pip install -r requirements.txt

Run the project using: uvicorn main:app --reload
By default the hosting will be at: http://127.0.0.1:8000
you can use any browser to access it

After having done with the use of the tool
To stop the project: ctrl+c
Deactivate the virtual environemnt: deactivate

When running the tool after hosting:
select document and click on upload and extract the document you like. it will take you to a: http://127.0.0.1:8000/upload
watch the "ok" status if it is true then the document are successfully uploaded in the local server and text extraction is successful
A "documents.db" file will be generated and "/uploads" folder will be created in the local directory from where the tool was hosted
Go back to the previous page and if under documents section your uploaded document is not visible then REFRESH the page and click on open button under view
